## Conclusion

This theater represents a carefully engineered reference-level system designed to deliver exceptional performance across all aspects: imaging, dynamics, bass extension, and immersion. Every design decision has been analyzed, calculated, and verified to ensure optimal results.

The Revision 5.2 design adds detailed LCR isolation specifications:
- Sorbothane 50 durometer hemispheres (1.5" diameter × 0.5" thick)
- 4 pucks per speaker in rectangular pattern (12 total for all LCR)
- Complete installation methodology and best practices documented
- Essential for reference-level imaging performance ($72-96 total investment)

The Revision 5.1 design provides critical documentation clarifications:
- High-pass filter standardized to 18-20Hz throughout (WinISD verified safe)
- LCR isolation elevated from "optional" to "standard" (essential for reference)
- Builder DIY capabilities documented (acoustic treatment, electrical work)
- Rear subwoofer placement clarified (hard against rear wall, floor-level, three-wall loading)
- Equipment rack spatial layout clarified (beside screen, not competing with LCR space)

The Revision 5.0 design upgrades Atmos speakers to eliminate the system's only performance weak link:
- DIYSG Volt-10 speakers (98 dB sensitivity verified)
- 107-108 dB capability at listening positions (exceeds THX Reference by +2-3 dB)
- Ensures all channels achieve reference capability with comfortable headroom
- Consistent no-compromise philosophy across entire system

The Revision 4 design refines the subwoofer dimensions for improved construction and serviceability:
- Front subs: 45"W × 21"H × 24"D (better driver spacing, easier handling)
- Rear subs: 24"W × 42"H × 22"D (matched volume, space savings)
- Improved clearances and more practical aspect ratios
- Maintains all acoustic performance targets (109 dB @ 20Hz at MLP)

The Revision 2 foundation optimizes the front stage configuration by:
- Integrating front subwoofers into floor-level corner pockets (three-wall loading)
- Positioning equipment rack on stage deck beside LCR (excellent access)
- Maintaining clean aesthetics (everything hidden behind AT fabric)
- Simplifying construction (no complex equipment bay cavities)

The 2027 construction timeline allows for thorough planning while technology matures. The fundamental designƒ×š¬³sealed subwoofers with corner loading, behind-screen LCR, advanced room correction, and tactile enhancementƒ×š¬³is based on proven principles that will remain valid.

Key success factors:
- Rigorous mathematical design (no guesswork)
- Quality components from established manufacturers
- Modular construction approach (manageable complexity)
- Professional calibration (maximize system potential)
- Safety margins in all subsystems (longevity and reliability)

The result will be a theater capable of THX reference levels with substantial headroom, true 20Hz extension, exceptional imaging from all seats, and a level of immersion that rivals commercial cinemasƒ×š¬³all in a dedicated, purpose-built environment optimized for the ultimate viewing experience.

**Total investment:** ~$75,250-92,969 (Rev 5.2, with DIY capabilities)
**Recommended budget:** $80,000-90,000 (includes 10% contingency)
**Timeline:** 2027 construction
**Expected lifespan:** 15-20+ years with proper maintenance
**Performance target:** 109 dB @ 20Hz at MLP (exceeds THX Reference by +4 dB)
**Peak capability:** 113+ dB @ 20Hz (for dynamic film transients)
**Atmos capability:** 107-108 dB at MLP (exceeds THX Reference by +2-3 dB)
**Driver operating point:** 600W per driver (93% of 28mm Xmax mechanical limit, WinISD verified)
**Amplifier headroom:** PURIFI monoblocks provide power beyond driver mechanical limits (proper engineering)
**Verified specifications:** All subwoofer calculations based on Dayton Audio official spec sheet and WinISD modeling

This document serves as both a construction guide and a knowledge repository, ensuring that when build time arrives, every decision has already been made with full understanding of the engineering trade-offs and rationale.

